FT  05 AUG 94 / Observer: Strung out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The whole world has gone roller-towel mad, as Observer's fax machine can
testify.
In the Department of Trade and Industry HQ in London, staff who need to wash
their hands can read the following, apparently genuine, notice on the wall:
'Fawlty towels service - call Basil on extension . . .'
