FT  05 AUG 94 / Observer: Sunday roast
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
One loss-making Lloyd's Name was asked what he was doing at yesterday's
press conference - on the subject of how the insurance market intended to
put the boot-boys in to collect its debts. 'If I'm going to be slaughtered,
I want to check the abattoir is up to EC standards'.
