<TEXT>
Sir, It is disturbing that such a large company as BT still feels unable to
plan its job reduction programme over a period of time and therefore avoid
any need for the unpleasantness and bad publicity that goes with compulsory
redundancy ('BT plans to shed 50,000 more jobs', August 1). It is
particularly noticeable that while Sir Iain Vallance talks of the need for a
further 50,000 job losses he suggests no valid reason as to why this might
be necessary. One would have thought that with the expansion of
telecommunications more rather than less staff might be a more sensible
forecast for the medium term.
