FT  04 AUG 94 / BT to cut cost of directory inquiries
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
British Telecommunications is cutting the cost of directory inquiries for UK
numbers, Alan Cane writes.
BT said yesterday that from September 1 calls to directory inquiries will
cost 25p including value added tax compared to the 44.2p now charged. BT
said technical improvements had made the cut possible. Charges were
introduced three years ago. Inquiries for international numbers will still
cost 44.42p.
Oftel, the industry watchdog, and the Telecommunications Users' Association
both welcomed the move.
The association said its research showed that 64 per cent of customers had
either stopped using the service or switched to a cheaper alternative since
the charges , thought to be among the highest in the world, were introduced.
