<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 94 / London Stock Exchange: NatWest surprises
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and SAQIB QURESHI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
High Street bank National Westminster surprised the market - but more
because of the performance of its shares than the details of its first half
profits. Once the reduction in the bad debt charge had been taken into
account underlying profits were down by 9 per cent.
However, the shares have fallen so far this year that by the time the
figures came out they looked very cheap. Analyst Mr Michael Lever of Nomura
said: 'It was the cheapest in the sector in p/e terms. The results were
disappointing in terms of underlying profits but this was more than
adequately compensated by the rating.'
The stock rose 17 to 470p, with a number of investors taking the opportunity
to close out their bear positions.
