<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 94 / World Commodities Prices: Minor Metals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
European free market, from Metal Bulletin, Dollars per lb in warehouse,
unless otherwise stated (last week's in brackets, where changed). Antimony:
99.6%, Dollars per tonne, 4,800-5,050. Bismuth: min. 99.99%, tonne lots
3.50-4.00 (3.60-4.20). Cadmium: min. 99.5%, 100-115 (95-105) cents a pound.
