<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 94 / International Capital Markets: Canadian Pacific advances to
CDollars 110m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Canadian Pacific, the transport, resources, hotel and property group, posted
net profit in the second quarter to June of CDollars 110.5m (USDollars 80m),
up from CDollars 29.6m a year earlier.
Including special items, final net profit was CDollars 198.4m, or 60 cents a
share, against CDollars 12m, or 3 cents. Consolidated revenues from
continuing operations were CDollars 1.9bn, against CDollars 1.65bn.
First-half final net profit was CDollars 215.6m, or 65 cents, against
CDollars 33.7m, or 10 cents, on revenues of CDollars 3.5bn against CDollars
3.13bn. The first quarter was adversely affected by the severe winter, but
second-quarter results were better than most analysts had estimated.
The half-year included a positive CDollars 9.5m contribution from Laidlaw,
the waste management group, against a negative CDollars 5.8m. However,
telecommunications losses were up sharply.
