<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 94 / International Company News: Agco impresses with a sharp rise
to Dollars 21.7m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Agco, the US farm machinery company which recently acquired Massey Ferguson,
reported second-quarter net earnings of Dollars 21.7m, or Dollars 1.53 a
share, on sales of Dollars 226m, up sharply from year-ago earnings of
Dollars 13.6m, or Dollars 1.18, on sales of Dollars 152m, writes Laurie
Morse in Chicago.
For the first six months of the year, Agco earned Dollars 36m or Dollars
2.56 a share, on sales of Dollars 405m, up from Dollars 18m or Dollars 1.87
a share on sales of Dollars 255m.
Cost-cutting and sales volume generated by Agco's acquisition of White-New
Idea, a US equipment maker, helped the result. Its Dollars 329m purchase of
Massey Ferguson's European operations did not close until June 29, so
second-quarter results reflect only one day of Massey's results.
</TEXT>
