<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Vivat down after exceptional
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After an exceptional Pounds 1m charge to cover the closure costs of its
Marseilles distribution centre, pre-tax profits at Vivat Holdings fell from
Pounds 1.84m to Pounds 1.06m in the six months to end-June.
Turnover declined by 12 per cent to Pounds 33.6m (Pounds 38.3m).
The drop in sales was because of organisational difficulties at the jeans
manufacturer's French subsidiary, but was partly offset by good performances
in Belgium, Spain and the UK.
The company also recently became aware of a long-standing under-statement of
stock in its Tunisian subsidiary.
The Pounds 3.5m under-statement has been dealt with as a prior year
adjustment to reserves, and has had no effect on the profit and loss account
since 1990.
Mr Christopher Burnett, chairman, said 'further clarification of the
circumstances is being sought'.
Earnings per share were 1.3p (2.4p).
