<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Edinburgh Small net asset value at 103p
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Edinburgh Small Companies Trust, admitted to the Official List in August
1993, reported a net asset value of 102.88p per share at June 30.
The trust, which aims for long-term capital growth through a portfolio of
small UK quoted companies, achieved net revenue of Pounds 373,000 for the
period from July 9 1993 to end-June 1994.
Earnings per share were 0.72p and a final distribution of 0.21p is
recommended.
Edinburgh New Tiger Trust, incorporated in January 1994 and launched in
March, announced a 6 per cent fall in net asset value to 45.28p from launch
to the end of June.
Net revenue amounted to Pounds 944,000 for earnings per share of 0.337p.
